  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nWhen OIDC is enabled and configured, we can authenticate on the Kubernetes API via Google Auth with any gmail address.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nWe should be able to limit access only to hosted domain addresses.\r\nWe could add an --oidc-hosted-domain flag for the API server, with the authorized domain in parameter. The authentication plugin would check the domain against the `hd` field in the id-token payload.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n- Create Google OAuth clientSecret and clientID.\r\n- Authenticate via Google and get OIDC token.\r\n- Update kubeconfig with a new user (the google authenticated user).\r\n\r\nAny gmail account can authenticate.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: AWS\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Debian\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): Linux 4.4.111-k8s\r\n- Install tools: kops\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n/sig auth",
